## Main prompt template for Magmathor environment.
##
## OPTIMIZED FOR PREFIX CACHING: Static content comes first so it can be
## cached across requests. Dynamic content (history, memories, plan) comes last.
##
## Condition Codes:
##   T0 = image mode, T1 = text mode
##   A1 = first action, A0 = not first action
##   R0 = no memory, R1 = use memory
##   S0 = single action, S1 = full steps (plan sequence)
##   Fn = feedback none, Fs = feedback simple, Fd = feedback detailed
##   I0 = no previous image, I1 = color previous, I2 = grayscale previous

## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
## STATIC BLOCK - Identical across ALL tasks and steps (best for caching)
## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Available Actions (always the same)
[--------
*       |
        | {include:available_actions.prompt}
--------]

## World Rules (always the same)
[--------
*       |
        | {include:world_rules.prompt}
--------]

## Task Instructions (always the same structure)
[--------
*       | {include:task_instructions.prompt}
--------]

## Examples (always the same - ~500 lines, biggest caching win!)
[--------
*       |
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | SECTION: EXAMPLES
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | {include:example1.prompt}
        | {include:example2.prompt}
        | {include:example3.prompt}
--------]

## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
## CACHE BOUNDARY MARKER - Everything above is static, everything below is dynamic
## For Anthropic models, content above this marker goes in system message with cache_control
## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
[--------
*       | <<CACHE_BOUNDARY>>
--------]

## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
## SEMI-STATIC BLOCK - Stable within a task run (secondary caching benefit)
## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Task intro and description
[--------
*       |
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | SECTION: YOUR TASK
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | You are acting inside a simulated 3D environment.
        | Your task is: {task_description}
        |
--------]

## Available objects for this task
[--------
*       |
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | SECTION: AVAILABLE OBJECTS
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | {objects_in_scene}
        |
--------]

## Image guidance (config-dependent)
[--------
*       | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | SECTION: IMAGE GUIDANCE
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
--------]

[--------
A0 T0 I2| - The first image (grayscale) shows the state of the world before the last action was attempted.
        | - The second image (color) shows the current state of the world (after the last action was attempted).
        | - Base all your scene observations on the SECOND (color) image.
A0 T0 I1| - The first image shows the state of the world before the last action was attempted.
        | - The second image shows the current state of the world (after the last action was attempted).
        | - Base all your scene observations on the SECOND image (current state).
A0 T0 I0| - Base your scene observations on the input image, which shows the current state of the world.
A0 T1   | - You are only using text input
A1 T0 I0| - Base your scene observations on the input image, which shows the current state of the world.
A1 T0 I1| - Base your scene observations on the input image, which shows the current state of the world.
A1 T0 I2| - Base your scene observations on the input image, which shows the current state of the world.
A1 T1   | - You are only using text input
--------]

## First action notice (A1 only)
[--------
A1      |
        | NOTE: This is the FIRST ACTION in the sequence.
        | There is NO previous action history and NO prior memory. Do not assume any past actions.
--------]

## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
## DYNAMIC BLOCK - Changes every step (no caching benefit, kept at end)
## ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Agent Notes (A0 only) - action history changes each step
[--------
A0      |
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        | SECTION: AGENT NOTES
        | ------------------------------------------------------------
        |
        | HISTORY OF ATTEMPTED ACTIONS:
        | {action_history}
--------]

## Suggested plan sequence (A0 + S1 only) - changes each step
[--------
A0 S1   |
        | SUGGESTED PLAN SEQUENCE (from your previous response):
        | {suggested_plan_sequence}
        |
        | NOTE: This was YOUR proposed plan from the previous step. Evaluate whether it still makes sense given what you observe now. Do NOT follow it blindly — adapt based on the current state.
--------]

## Memory from previous step (A0 + R1 only) - changes each step
[--------
A0 R1   |
        | MEMORY FROM PREVIOUS STEP:
        | {memories}
--------]
